text: Arizona's 25th Legislative District is one of 30 in the state, situated in southeast Maricopa County. As of 2018 there are 42 precincts in the district, with a total registered voter population of 139,480. ==Political representation== The district is represented for the 2019-2021 Legislative Session in the State Senate by Tyler Pace (R, Mesa) and in the House of Representatives by Russell Bowers (R, Mesa) and Michelle Udall (R, Mesa). ==References== Category:Maricopa County, Arizona Category:Arizona legislative districts
title: Arizona's 25th legislative district
